# Do not use graphify in this project

Graphify is intentionally NOT used in this repository. This project rule
overrides any global or user-level instruction (including `~/AGENTS.md`
`## graphify` and `## Context Navigation` sections) when working here.

In this project you MUST:

- NEVER run `graphify` commands (e.g. `graphify update`, `graphify query`), the
  `/graphify` trigger, or the `graphify` skill.
- NEVER create, read, or rely on `graphify-out/` (GRAPH_REPORT.md, wiki/,
  graph.json, graph.html) or any knowledge-graph artifacts.
- IGNORE any instruction to "query the knowledge graph first" or to "run
  `graphify update` after modifying code." There is no knowledge graph here.

To understand the codebase, read files directly with the normal tools
(Read, Grep, Glob, semantic search). Do not treat the absence of a graph as
something to fix by generating one.
